module.m4.body:
DDL commands define database structure.

CREATE TABLE adds a new table with column definitions:
CREATE TABLE users (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT);

ALTER TABLE adds or removes columns from an existing table:
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN email TEXT;

DROP TABLE permanently deletes a table and all its data:
DROP TABLE users;

module.m7.body:
Subqueries help filter by computed sets or single values.

IN: match rows where a column is in a subquery result.
SELECT name FROM customers WHERE id IN (SELECT customer_id FROM orders);

Scalar: compare against a single computed value.
SELECT name FROM customers WHERE id = (SELECT customer_id FROM orders ORDER BY total DESC LIMIT 1);

EXISTS: returns true if the subquery finds at least one row.
SELECT name FROM customers WHERE EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM orders WHERE orders.customer_id = customers.id);
